title: Macquarie Dictionary announces ‘AI slop’ as its word of the year, beating out Ozempic face
summary: The term "ate that and left no crumbs" was selected as the 2023 Word of the Year by a panel, competing against options like "Ozempic face," "blind box," and "Roman Empire." This reflects the cultural conversations around food and social media trends. The chosen phrase emphasizes confident enjoyment and leaving no waste behind.

title: Brisbane storms and hail leave nearly 100,000 without power as trees downed and roofs stripped
summary: Severe winds were the primary cause of power outages in the city, affecting numerous residents. In addition, the area experienced over 880,000 lightning strikes and hail up to 12 centimeters in diameter. The extreme weather condition significantly impacted local infrastructure and safety.

title: Canada: ‘Inconvenient Indian’ author Thomas King says he is not Indigenous
summary: King announced that a genealogist, working with the Tribal Alliance Against Frauds, found no evidence of Cherokee ancestry in his family lineage. This conclusion comes after scrutiny over claims of Indigenous heritage. The findings have significant implications for ongoing discussions about identity and representation.
